[[PHASE_1]]
===STEP SHELL COMMAND PARSER & DISPATCHER===
Replace hard-coded if/else with: tokenizer (lex args into argc/argv), command table (struct{name,handler,arity,help,classification:native|bridge-only}), arg packing for z_spawn (pack argv into single string, unpack on spawn). Add commands: ENV, EXPORT, ALIAS, HISTORY, WHOAMI, PWD, CD, LS, CAT, EXIT. All new commands are "native". Add tab-completion against command table. Add command history ring buffer with persistence. Add line editing (cursor move, insert/delete at cursor). Preserve to_upper() on command names. Hyphens permitted in input arguments. PKG_* bridge-only commands convert argument uppercase to lowercase before forwarding via Z_UI_CMD_BRIDGE_DATA.
===/STEP===

[[PHASE_1_CONSTRAINTS]]
C1 binary cap <= 32768 bytes (report in VERIFICATION). C2 freestanding (headers: zenith/user.h, stdint.h, stdbool.h, stddef.h ONLY). C3 single-arg spawn. C4 64-byte IPC. C7 no new syscalls. C10 single address space. C12 bridge-only commands must not call z_open/z_read/z_close. All static alloc. Tab-completion within existing buffer. to_upper() preserved for native commands.
[[/PHASE_1_CONSTRAINTS]]

[[PHASE_1_VERIFY]]
VC-1:
(a) Every command in table executes with valid+invalid args.
(b) Tab-completion covers full command set.
(c) z_spawn arg packing roundtrips correctly.
(d) Static allocation unchanged — no malloc.
(e) Command classification: every command labeled native|bridge-only. Bridge-only commands verified zero z_open/z_read/z_close calls.
(f) to_upper() preserved for native commands. PKG_* arguments upper→lower before bridge forwarding.
COMPLIANCE_ENGINE checklist applied to every new/modified function.
Binary size reported: N/32768 bytes.
[[/PHASE_1_VERIFY]]

[[PHASE_1_EVIDENCE_REQUIREMENTS]]
- Command table struct: {name, classification, handler, arity, help}
- Diff summary: functions added, functions modified, lines changed
- Binary size: integer byte count after llvm-objcopy -O binary
[[/PHASE_1_EVIDENCE_REQUIREMENTS]]

---SPECIFICATION---
<FILE path="{{KERNEL_SOURCE}}">{{FULL_SOURCE}}</FILE>
<SYSCALL>none new</SYSCALL>
<VERIFY>VC-1a..VC-1f: PASS|FAIL — evidence per item</VERIFY>
