[[/PHASE_1]]

[[PHASE_2]]
===STEP I/O REDIRECTION & PIPE FOUNDATION===
New syscalls: SYS_PIPE(fds[2]), SYS_DUP2(old,new), SYS_GETPID(), SYS_GETPPID(). Shell operators: > (redirect stdout to file), >> (append), < (stdin from file), | (pipe between commands). Shell pipe support: implement fork-exec pattern — fork → child dup2s FDs → exec → parent waits. Wire pipe syscall to kernel IPC. Handle PIPE_BUF fragmentation for 64-byte IPC cap (chunked reads with length prefix). Split-pane layout is a SEPARATE concern (Phase 4 UI feature) — do NOT implement split-pane here. This phase implements ONLY the shell | operator and underlying pipe syscall.

Pipe implementation under C11 bridge architecture: pipe data flows through kernel-managed buffers via existing IPC. No shared memory mapping. No file pipes. 64-byte IPC frame enforces natural truncation for pipe reads.
===/STEP===

[[PHASE_2_CONSTRAINTS]]
C1 binary cap <= 32768 bytes. C4 64-byte IPC — pipe reads chunked (56-byte payload max, 8-byte header). C7 syscall numbers start at 28. C8 hybrid kernel — pipe allocates kernel-managed buffer, not per-process ring. C10 single address space — pipe is kernel-mediated copy, not shared memory. C11 bridge architecture enforced — no shared memory mapping, no file pipes. Freestanding headers only.
[[/PHASE_2_CONSTRAINTS]]

[[PHASE_2_VERIFY]]
VC-2:
(a) echo hello > file.txt -> file contains "hello\n".
(b) cat < file.txt -> prints file contents.
(c) cmd1 | cmd2 -> cmd2 receives cmd1 stdout.
(d) 4KB pipe transfer completes with zero data loss.
(e) Pipe FDs closed on process exit — no leaks.
(f) No shared memory mapping, no file pipes, no mmap — pipe is kernel-mediated IPC copy only.
COMPLIANCE_ENGINE checklist applied to every new/modified function.
Binary size reported: N/32768 bytes.
[[/PHASE_2_VERIFY]]

[[PHASE_2_EVIDENCE_REQUIREMENTS]]
- Syscall table additions: {number, name, signature, purpose}
- Pipe buffer size and chunk protocol specification
- Binary size: integer byte count after llvm-objcopy -O binary
[[/PHASE_2_EVIDENCE_REQUIREMENTS]]

---SPECIFICATION---
<FILE path="{{KERNEL_SOURCE}}">{{FULL_SOURCE}}</FILE>
<SYSCALL>SYS_PIPE=28 SYS_DUP2=29 SYS_GETPID=30 SYS_GETPPID=31</SYSCALL>
<VERIFY>VC-2a..VC-2f: PASS|FAIL — evidence per item</VERIFY>
<SUMMARY>syscall additions, pipe buffer size, chunk protocol, binary size</SUMMARY>
---/SPECIFICATION---
[[/PHASE_2]]

[[PHASE_3]]
===STEP PACKAGE MANAGEMENT & REPOSITORY SYSTEM===
Build zpkg: install/remove/update/search/list/info. sources.list at /etc/apt/sources.list.d/zenith-local.list -> file://{{REPO_DIR}}. .deb unpacker (ar+tar). SAT resolver for dependency graph with cycle detection using these pinned test fixtures:
- Fixture A: A->B->C->A (simple cycle) — must detect and report cycle.
- Fixture B: A->B->C + A->C (diamond) — must resolve without false cycle detection.
- Fixture C: 26-node chain (A->B->...->Z) — must resolve depth without stack overflow.

Transaction atomicity: snapshot dpkg state pre-mutate, rewrite on failure. Wire to {{WS_PACKAGES}}. Build pipeline: {{PKG_BUILD}} scans {{PKG_MANIFEST}}, builds .deb set, generates Packages.gz + Release + InRelease (GPG sign — fail build on missing key, never skip).

Case conversion rule (CE-8): to_upper() preserved on kernel terminal command names. PKG_INSTALL/PKG_SEARCH/PKG_INFO convert argument uppercase to lowercase before forwarding to bridge. Hyphens permitted in package name arguments (e.g., PKG_INSTALL ZENITH-FILES → zenith-files).
===/STEP===

[[PHASE_3_CONSTRAINTS]]
C6 original code only. C5 initramfs read-only — packages install to writable mount. All mutations require user confirmation. Rollback snapshot must be atomic (write temp, rename). No network at build time. Flatpak deferred to runtime. C4 paged sub-protocol for PKG_INFO/PKG_SEARCH kernel terminal commands (56-byte max payload per IPC, KEY_DOWN advances page).
[[/PHASE_3_CONSTRAINTS]]

[[PHASE_3_VERIFY]]
VC-3:
(a) Fixture A (A->B->C->A) -> cycle error, not infinite recursion.
(b) Fixture B (A->B->C + A->C diamond) -> resolves correctly, no false cycle detection.
(c) Fixture C (26-node chain A->Z) -> resolves depth without stack overflow.
(d) Install --dry-run then real install -> binary exists at /usr/bin/.
(e) Remove with reverse-depends flagged -> user warned.
(f) Rollback restores prior dpkg state.
(g) GPG missing -> build fails, not silent skip.
(h) 50-package chain resolves.
(i) PKG_INFO/PKG_SEARCH paged output: first IPC returns line_count + first line, subsequent KEY_DOWN advances, never exceeds 56 bytes payload.
COMPLIANCE_ENGINE: not applicable (Python phase), but verify no forbidden patterns per AP3.
[[/PHASE_3_VERIFY]]

[[PHASE_3_EVIDENCE_REQUIREMENTS]]
- Resolver strategy description
- Test fixture results: fixture ID, input graph, expected outcome, actual outcome
- Repo layout: directory tree with file counts
[[/PHASE_3_EVIDENCE_REQUIREMENTS]]

---SPECIFICATION---
<FILE path="{{WS_PACKAGES}}">{{FULL_SOURCE}}</FILE>
<FILE path="{{PKG_BUILD}}">{{SCRIPT}}</FILE>
<FILE path="{{PKG_MANIFEST}}">{{MANIFEST}}</FILE>
<VERIFY>VC-3a..VC-3i: PASS|FAIL — evidence per item</VERIFY>
<SUMMARY>zpkg commands, resolver strategy, repo layout, fixture results</SUMMARY>
---/SPECIFICATION---
[[/PHASE_3]]

[[PHASE_4]]
===STEP TERMINAL EMULATOR UPGRADE===
Scrollback buffer (1000 lines default, configurable to 10000). ANSI escape state-machine parser (CSI sequences: cursor, color, clear, scroll regions). Line editing: readline-equivalent (Ctrl-A/E, Ctrl-U/K, Ctrl-R reverse search, arrow history). Command history with persistence to disk. Tab completion against command table + filesystem paths. Decouple terminal rendering from shell logic — terminal owns display, shell owns execution. Add color profile engine (zenith-dark default, zenith-light, solarized, custom from ~/.config/zenith-terminal/profiles.json). Fail closed on malformed JSON -> fallback zenith-dark. URL detection + clickable links. Search-within-scrollback (regex).

Split-pane layout: horizontal/vertical split as standalone UI feature. Synchronized input broadcast to panes. Shell pipe support (| operator) is SEPARATE from split-pane — pipe is kernel-space IPC (Phase 2), split-pane is UI layout (this phase). Do not conflate.
===/STEP===

[[PHASE_4_CONSTRAINTS]]
No new Python packages beyond stdlib+gi. No compiled extensions. Per-tab memory <20MB. ANSI parser must be state-machine, not regex. Color profile parse fails closed.
[[/PHASE_4_CONSTRAINTS]]

[[PHASE_4_VERIFY]]
VC-4:
(a) 10 tabs open+close -> zero zombie PIDs.
(b) Malformed JSON profile -> zenith-dark fallback.
(c) ANSI escape stress test (1000 mixed sequences) -> zero parser crash.
(d) Ctrl-R reverse search finds history entry.
(e) Tab-completion against /usr/bin/ prefix.
(f) Split pane receives synchronized input.
(g) Shell pipe (|) and split-pane are architecturally separate — no pipe logic in split-pane code, no split-pane logic in pipe code.
[[/PHASE_4_VERIFY]]

[[PHASE_4_EVIDENCE_REQUIREMENTS]]
- Scrollback size configuration
- ANSI parser state count
- Color profile list and fallback behavior
- Feature list split: shell-pipe features vs split-pane features (no overlap)
[[/PHASE_4_EVIDENCE_REQUIREMENTS]]

---SPECIFICATION---
<FILE path="{{WS_TERMINAL}}">{{FULL_SOURCE}}</FILE>
<VERIFY>VC-4a..VC-4g: PASS|FAIL — evidence per item</VERIFY>
<SUMMARY>scrollback size, ANSI states, profile count, feature list</SUMMARY>
---/SPECIFICATION---
[[/PHASE_4]]

[[PHASE_5]]
===STEP INTEGRATION, STRESS TESTING & HARDENING===
Add SYS_REBOOT, SYS_CHDIR, SYS_GETCWD syscalls. Environment variables (setenv/getenv in shell). End-to-end tests:
(1) Kernel terminal PKG_INSTALL zenith-files -> verify binary at /usr/bin/zenith-files.
(2) Workstation zenesh --command "zpkg install hello && hello" -> verify VTE output.
(3) 4KB bridge output -> verify truncation to TERM_CAP.
(4) Kill userspace -> kernel prints BRIDGE TIMEOUT within 2s.
(5) Stress: 10 tabs, 50 pipes, 100-package resolve, 1000 ANSI sequences simultaneously.

Bridge verification (CHECKPOINT_ZETA): Bridge verification MUST include first 16 bytes hex of received kernel-terminal output, manually compared against expected output. No PASS based on log statements alone. Verification protocol:
  Step 1: Send command via bridge.
  Step 2: Receive response via Z_UI_CMD_BRIDGE_DATA.
  Step 3: Extract first 16 bytes of payload.
  Step 4: Convert to hex string (32 hex chars).
  Step 5: Compare against expected hex value.
  Step 6: Match = PASS. Mismatch = FAIL with both hex strings logged.

Paged PKG_INFO/PKG_SEARCH E2E test: issue PKG_INFO from kernel terminal, verify first IPC contains line_count + first line, verify subsequent KEY_DOWN events advance pages, verify no payload exceeds 56 bytes.

Constraint audit: C1-C12 all satisfied. Dependency ceiling: no new deps beyond existing {{VERSION}} workstation build.
===/STEP===

[[PHASE_5_CONSTRAINTS]]
C1-C12 full audit. Bridge must never block kernel IPC loop. Userspace absent -> kernel degrades gracefully ("USERSPACE UNAVAILABLE"). Bridged output truncated to TERM_CAP. C4 paged sub-protocol for PKG_INFO/PKG_SEARCH enforced. C11 bridge via Z_UI_CMD_BRIDGE_DATA only — no shared memory, no file pipes. SIGHUP to all child PIDs on window close. Freestanding headers only.
[[/PHASE_5_CONSTRAINTS]]

[[PHASE_5_VERIFY]]
VC-5:
(a) All C1-C12 satisfied.
(b) Both E2E paths succeed with byte-level hex verification (first 16 bytes).
(c) Bridge timeout fires within 2s.
(d) Stress test completes with zero crashes.
(e) Zero new external dependencies.
(f) Zero zombie PIDs post-close.
(g) Paged PKG_INFO/PKG_SEARCH: verify line_count in first IPC, page advance on KEY_DOWN, payload <= 56 bytes.
(h) Binary size reported: N/32768 bytes.
COMPLIANCE_ENGINE checklist applied to every new/modified C function.
[[/PHASE_5_VERIFY]]

[[PHASE_5_EVIDENCE_REQUIREMENTS]]
- Final syscall table: complete array
- Constraint compliance: 12-row table
- Bridge hex verification: expected_hex, actual_hex, match: bool
- Binary size: integer byte count after llvm-objcopy -O binary
- Paged protocol test: page_count, payload_sizes (all must be <= 56)
[[/PHASE_5_EVIDENCE_REQUIREMENTS]]

---SPECIFICATION---
